From a089c8f13a365c4e67d98f92b95e2808978bb13e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Jun 2025 09:57:38 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: iw: Add support for displaying NO-IR
 regulatory flag

Currently, iw reg get command does not have support for
displaying information about the NO-IR flags for the regulatory
rules. The current assumption that modern kernel always set
both NL80211_RRF_NO_IR and __NL80211_RRF_NO_IBSS is not correct
as __NL80211_RRF_NO_IBSS is deprecated and may not be set
in the kernel.

To fix this, add support for displaying the reg rules as NO-IR
based on the regulatory flag - NL80211_RRF_NO_IR alone, which
works for both modern and legacy kernels.
  (1) Both NL80211_RRF_PASSIVE_SCAN (set by older kernel) and
      NL80211_RRF_NO_IR (set by modern kernel) are displayed
      as NO-IR.
  (2) __NL80211_RRF_NO_IBSS is displayed as NO-IBSS if it is
      set by the older kernel.

Signed-off-by: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 reg.c | 15 ++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/reg.c b/reg.c
index 3e6e843539bd..71969bc31e3a 100644
--- a/reg.c
+++ b/reg.c
@@ -246,13 +246,14 @@ static int print_reg_handler(struct nl_msg *msg, void *arg)
 		PARSE_FLAG(NL80211_RRF_NO_320MHZ, "NO-320MHZ");
 		PARSE_FLAG(NL80211_RRF_NO_EHT, "NO-EHT");
 
-		/* Kernels that support NO_IR always turn on both flags */
-		if ((flags & NL80211_RRF_NO_IR) && (flags & __NL80211_RRF_NO_IBSS)) {
-			printf(", NO-IR");
-		} else {
-			PARSE_FLAG(NL80211_RRF_PASSIVE_SCAN, "PASSIVE-SCAN");
-			PARSE_FLAG(__NL80211_RRF_NO_IBSS, "NO-IBSS");
-		}
+		/*
+		 * Latest kernels define NO_IR as the canonical flag.
+		 * Use the modern NO-IR flag if it is set, even for older
+		 * kernels that indicate it with PASSIVE-SCAN.
+		 */
+		PARSE_FLAG(NL80211_RRF_NO_IR, "NO-IR");
+		/* For backward compatibility */
+		PARSE_FLAG(__NL80211_RRF_NO_IBSS, "NO-IBSS");
 
 		printf("\n");
 	}
